07/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic said on Sunday (September 6th) that police have managed to thwart several planned murders by arresting members of a dangerous criminal gang led by Darko Elez. In all, 22 members were arrested on September 1st, in a joint operation by Serbian and Bosnian police. Two more people were arrested later. Eight members, including Elez, a Bosnian national, were detained in Serbia while the others were arrested in Bosnia and Herzegovina. Some media have speculated that the gang planned to assassinate politicians and officials in Serbia. (Tanjug, B92 - 06/09/09)
